{{multiple issues| {{Orphan|date=January 2016}} {{expand Russian|topic=geo|date=January 2016}} }} '''Auh''' is a historical [[Chechens|Chechen]] settlement in [[Dagestan]].
== History == In 1921, Auh was included in the [[Dagestan Autonomous Soviet Socialist Republic|Dagestan ASSR]], despite the desire of Akkins to join the [[Chechen-Ingush Autonomous Soviet Socialist Republic]]. According to another explanation, the reason was the entering Akkins fear of losing their winter pastures in the territory of the [[Khasavyurtovsky District]]. In 1943, the territory was incorporated into the Auha Auhovsky area. In 1944 Akkin Chechens were deported to Central Asia. The area of the historic residence was renamed the [[Novolaksky District]] and inhabited by [[Laks (Caucasus)|Laks]]. The [[yurt]] villages Auch and Auch-Aktas were transferred to the [[Kazbekovski District]] and inhabited by [[Avars (Caucasus)|Avars]]. In 1956, the Chechens (including the Akkin) began to return to their historical homeland.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://joshuaproject.net/people_groups/20318/RS |title=Akkin in Russia |author=|date= |website=joshuaproject.net |publisher=Joshua Project |access-date=February 26, 2016 |quote=}}</ref>
The Chechens' homes were located in the mountains, next to the [[Caspian Sea]]. In 1718 the [[Don Cossacks|Don cossacks]] were sent to destroy their houses and many were killed.<ref>[http://dlib.rsl.ru/viewer/01004102182#?page=565 Историческое описание российской коммерции при всех портах и границах : От древних времян до ныне настоящаго и всех преимущественных узаконений по оной государя имп. Петра Великаго и ныне благополучно царствующей государыни имп. Екатерины Великия, / Сочиненное Михайлом Чулковым. — Санктпетербург : При Имп. Акад. наук, 1781—1788. — 4°. Т.2, кн.2. — 1785. — 90, 1-446, 449—626 &#91;=624&#93; с. Хранение: MK АН-4°/ 81-Ч; Хранение: W 213/831; ]</ref><ref>[http://www.vostlit.info/Texts/Dokumenty/Kavkaz/XVIII/1720-1740/Gerber_Johann_Gustav/text4.htm ИОГАНН ГУСТАВ ГЕРБЕР ИЗВЕСТИЯ О НАХОДЯЩИХСЯ С ЗАПАДНОЙ СТОРОНЫ КАСПИЙСКОГО МОРЯ МЕЖДУ АСТРАХАНЬЮ И РЕКОЙ КУРОЙ НАРОДАХ И ЗЕМЛЯХ И О ИХ СОСТОЯНИИ В 1728 ГОДУ]</ref> == The mountains == [[Alburi Lam]] — mountain top in Akh. ==Gallery== <gallery perrow=12 widths="200px" heights="200px"> file:Gora Gebek-kala.jpg| file:Ярыксуаух Гачалка.jpg| file:Зориотар.jpg| file:Reka Aktash.jpg| file:Сала-су.jpg| file:Мечеть в Юртаухе.jpg| file:Старинная мечеть в Акташ-Аухе.jpg| </gallery>
